XXXVII. ¹Ay9eremjacere.] Aggeres were mounds or banks of earth thrown up, and raised to such a height, that they equalled or exceeded the height of the town walls. From these the soldiers dis- charged their missive weapons upon the inhabitants, and so protected their own men from their assaults, till they had time to undermine the wall, or beat it down with engines.-M.
